    <descriptionarticle only="false">
      <p>
        <text>As is obvious from the title, this object is used to <b>interrupt</b> execution of the program (or events, conditions or cycle).
        <b>To interrupt</b> means <b>not to execute</b> actions which <b>follow</b> the command of interruption.</text>
      </p>
      <p>
        <textAll>
          For example, if we create a command
          <link file="UsefulObjects/Interrupts/PropertiesCommands/Break event.html">Break event</link>,
          then all actions specified in this event <b>after</b> the command  Break event are <b>not</b> to be executed.
          The command <link file="UsefulObjects/Interrupts/PropertiesCommands/Break application.html">Break application</link> <b> closes</b> your program (Exit).
        </textAll>
      </p>
